RACE.RACE_TEXT: Buzz Bar S. FONNER PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Stakes Purse 19800. FOR NEBRASKA BRED COLTS AND GELDINGS, THREE YEAR OLDS. PURSE $20,000-added. No nomination fee. $50 to pass the entry box and an additional $50 to start. Weight: 122 lbs. Non-winners of three races allowed 2 lbs. Non-winners of two races allowed 4 lbs. Mai dens allowed 6 lbs. High Weights Preferred. Total earnings will be used in determining the order of preference of horses assigned equal weights. Closed Friday, May 5 with four nominations.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHIPS LOG dueled on the early lead inside a rival while out from the rail, kicked clear in the final turn then held safe under steady handling in the lane. MO SUMMER drifted out a bit in the first turn, settled to stalking position four wide and made a mild gain but could not threaten the winner. J PS HARLEY GLIDER dueled on the lead outside the winner to late backstretch and came up empty nearing the lane. BUY NOW saved ground and trailed.

ENTRY.NAME: Mo Summer
ENTRY.OWNER: Larmon Julie and Schliefert Bradley D

ENTRY.NAME: Ships Log
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled off rail inside rival, kicked clear, held safe lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FONNER PARK RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 4559. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUCKENBACHER broke in the air but quickly recovered to prompt the pace three and four wide, challenged outside PRAIRIE SQUALL through the far turn, then dueled that one through the lane and surged late to be narrowly up at the wire. PRAIRIE SQUALL gained the early lead to establish position inside, was pressed throughout, dug in as the winner challenged nearing the lane to duel to the end but came up short. SPEEDY FELLAR tracked from between rivals to the far turn and weakened. GONE PREACHIN leaned into the side of the gate to get away last, stalked inside, angled four wide nearing the lane but had no rally.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZ BRIGHTER gained a short early lead inside rivals going to the first turn, drew off heading up the backstretch then held the margin throughout under steady handling. RACE.FOOTNOTES: SWEETNESS TO was in reach of the pace three to four wide to move closer into the lane, responded when set down and rallied clear under urging. RACE.FOOTNOTES: S C ANGEL showed the most early speed to gain inside position, made the pace then angled out nearing the lane to about the four path and held safe under steady handling. AUNT IRENE moved two and three wide to bid outside the winner into the far turn then could not go with that one in the lane while clearly best of the others. STARLIGHT TWIST was slow into stride to drop off the early pace saving ground, angled four wide nearing the lane moved up while not a threat. HARLONS COMMISION forced the pace outside the winner to the far turn and faded in the lane. NINA EN FUEGO was not a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: COMPETITIVE SPIRIT was back off the pace three or four wide to the far turn, angled in nearing the lane to rally up the rail and collared the leaders through the closing sixteenth. CHARACTER COUNTS was on the pace three and four wide to edge clear into the lane but could not hold the winner late. MISS JET rallied four wide into the far turn to move up and continued on to gain the show while unable to reach the top pair. CHAMA saved ground back off the pace, angled out into the lane and rallied late. SPITFIRE SUZIE was with the leaders three to four wide to the far turn and faded in the drive. EXODUS AND HOPE moved up four and five wide with a bid into the far turn and could not sustain the run. PIZZA GIRL drifted out into the first turn while showing speed and tired.
